# YAML Configuration Conventions

## Core Config Files

| File | Purpose | Repo |
|---|---|---|
| `iron.yml` | Master client config (catalog, compute, review settings) | iron-client-template |
| `review-standards/client.yml` | BLOCK/WARN/NOTE rules for the client | iron-client-template |
| `review-standards/default.yml` | Platform-wide default review rules | ironpilot |
| `databricks.yml` | Databricks Asset Bundle config | ironlayer-infra |
| `workspace.yml` | Workspace manifest | iron-dev-workspace |
| `dbt_project.yml` | dbt project config | ironlayer-infra/dbt-framework |
| `config.yaml` | SQLMesh project config (gateway, connections, model defaults) | SQLMesh client repos |

## Formatting Rules

- 2-space indentation for all YAML files
- Strings with special characters must be quoted
- Lists use `- item` on new lines (not inline `[a, b, c]` except for short arrays)
- Block scalars for multiline strings: `|` (literal) or `>` (folded)
- Always use explicit types where ambiguous (e.g., quote `"true"`, `"1.0"`)

## dbt YAML Schema

```yaml
version: 2

models:
  - name: fct_trades
    description: |
      One row per executed trade.
      Grain: trade_id (unique per execution).
    config:
      materialized: incremental
      unique_key: trade_id
      schema: gold
    columns:
      - name: trade_id
        description: "Surrogate key (order_id + fill_id)"
        tests:
          - unique
          - not_null
      - name: traded_at
        description: "UTC timestamp of trade execution"
        tests:
          - not_null
      - name: usd_amount
        description: "Trade value in USD"
        tests:
          - not_null
          - positive_value
```

## Databricks Asset Bundle Config

```yaml
# databricks.yml
bundle:
  name: iron-{client}

workspace:
  host: ${var.databricks_host}

variables:
  databricks_host:
    description: Databricks workspace URL
  client_id:
    description: Client identifier
    default: client-alpha

targets:
  dev:
    mode: development
    workspace:
      root_path: /Users/${workspace.current_user.userName}/.bundle/${bundle.name}/dev
    variables:
      client_id: client-alpha

  staging:
    mode: development
    workspace:
      root_path: /Shared/iron/staging

  production:
    mode: production
    workspace:
      root_path: /Shared/iron/prod
    run_as:
      service_principal_name: iron-service-principal
```

## GitHub Actions Workflow YAML

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]
  push:
    branches: [main]

permissions:
  contents: read
  pull-requests: write    # for PR review comments
  checks: write           # for check run reporting

jobs:
  lint:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v3
        with: { version: "latest" }
      - run: uv run ruff check .
      - run: uv run mypy . --ignore-missing-imports

  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    needs: lint
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: astral-sh/setup-uv@v3
        with: { version: "latest" }
      - run: uv run pytest tests/unit/ -v --tb=short --cov={package}
```

## SQLMesh Config Schema

```yaml
# config.yaml (SQLMesh project root)
gateways:
  databricks:
    connection:
      type: databricks
      server_hostname: "${DATABRICKS_HOST}"
      http_path: "${DATABRICKS_HTTP_PATH}"
      access_token: "${DATABRICKS_TOKEN}"
      catalog: "${CLIENT_ID}_prod"

default_gateway: databricks

model_defaults:
  dialect: databricks
  owner: "data-team@{client}.com"

variables:
  client: "{client_id}"
  environment: dev

format:
  normalize: true
  indent: 2
  max_line_length: 120
```

**Note:** `config.yaml` must never contain hardcoded credentials. Reference `${ENV_VAR}` syntax or env vars only.

## Environment Variable References in YAML

```yaml
# Use ${var.name} in Databricks bundles
host: ${var.databricks_host}

# Use ${{ secrets.NAME }} in GitHub Actions
env:
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}
  DATABRICKS_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.DATABRICKS_TOKEN }}

# Never hardcode credentials in YAML files
# Always reference environment variables or secrets managers
```
